<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/463> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #463" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.61.1; Diod. 14.17.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -]) Iulus II; [- -Capit]olin. Barb[at.]; [- -Cinc]innatus II; the others entire, Furius with numeral II); Chr. 354 (Iulo II et Mamertino); Degrassi 28f., 98, 380f. These began the siege of Veii (Liv. 4.61.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/462> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #462" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. gives the number as six, but omits Cincinnatus, Furius, and Aemilius; and has Mamilius for Manlius. On T. Quinctius see 421; he was Capitolini f. (Liv. 4.43.1). For Iulius' cognomen, see 489, note 1 (Tullus, Liv.; Iulus, Fast. Cap.). On Furius, see 413, note 1; the numeral in Livy is tertium. Livy's praenomen for Aemilius, M., is corrected to M'. as in Fast. Cap.; for his cognomen Livy has Mamercus. These magistrates are differently ordered in each of our three chief sources. Livy's order is followed above." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/430> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #430" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.49.1; Diod. 13.34.1; Fast. Cap. (P. Cornelius [A. f.] P. n. [- -]; C. Valerius L. f. Volusi n. [- -]); Chr. 354 (Casso et Cincinnato); Degrassi 26f., 97, 378f. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 36, no. 5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/429> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #429" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fabius has the praenomen Gaius in Diod., and M. in the Mss of Livy. See however 421, note 1; Fast. Cap. on 407, and Conway and Walters on Liv. 4.43.1, 49.1, 57.12, and 58.6. The filiation of Valerius, given in Fast. Cap. here, on 407, and 404, is doubted by Münzer (Gent. Val. 36, no. 5) who supplies P. n., as in that of L. Valerius, Mil. Tr. c. p. 414, 406." .
